snippet.title: University of Notre Dame
snippet.description: The University of Notre Dame, founded in 1842 by a priest of the Congregation of Holy Cross, is an independent, national Catholic university located in Notre Dame, Indiana, adjacent to the city of South Bend and approximately 90 miles east of Chicago.
